body:
The 33-bit wire was accidentally passed as an argument:
```
xmodule m(
	  {~xwire[31], xwire[31:0]}
);
```
for a 32-bit argument:
```
module xmodule(
  arg1
);
input     [31:0] arg1;
```
and no error was generated.

I couldn't find if this should or shouldn't be allowed in Verilog.

But if this situation could be caught by verilator this could save time.
